    "narrative": "The **Austin Waves** enter today\u2019s slate with a clear focal point at the top of the order: **Gunnar Henderson** stands as our premier play with a massive 81.88 score. His matchup against Teng is ideal, bolstered significantly by a +16% park factor and a +14% platoon advantage that vaults him into elite territory. He is joined by **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (72.10) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (70.66), both of whom benefit from favorable matchups against Holmes and Tolle, respectively. **Kyle Tucker** also remains a high-floor anchor at 69.49; despite his neutral platoon profile today, his consistent xwOBA metrics against Janson Junk make him a lock for our lineup.\n\nThe most difficult personnel decision involved the bench, where **Josh Jung** (50.73) fell just short of displacing **Dominic Smith** (48.11). While **Dominic Smith** carries a lower raw score, the optimizer favored his specific platoon matchup against Mize over the relative neutrality of the Schlittler-versus-**Josh Jung** engagement. Furthermore, we are monitoring **Brady House** (56.79) closely; while his strong platoon edge is promising, the defensive capability of the opposing pitcher\u2014a 53% SB suppression rate\u2014dampens his utility given our league's obsession with stolen base efficiency. \n\nBeyond these starters, we are exercising discipline with our bench depth to preserve our precious game caps. While **Nasim Nunez** and **Coby Mayo** possess intriguing profiles, their lower batting order placements drastically reduced their projected output, forcing them into reserve roles alongside **Miguel Vargas**. We remain confident in this high-ceiling configuration, though we are tracking weather reports for any late-breaking developments that could jeopardize the viability of our secondary outfielders, particularly **Andy Pages** and **Dominic Smith**, who are hovering near the floor of our utility threshold.",
